 Sarah Davis - Symptoms:

Shortness of breath, especially during physical activities.

 Cyanosis (bluish tint to the skin or lips) in severe cases.

Mark Lee - Diseased Heart Muscle (Cardiomyopathy) 

Overview: Mark Lee, a 45-year-old accountant, has been diagnosed with cardiomyopathy, a condition that results in the weakening of the heart muscle, leading to impaired heart function.

 Mark Lee - Symptoms: Shortness of breath, particularly during physical activities, Persistent fatigue and weakness, and Swelling in the ankles and abdomen.

 Mark Lee - Diagnosis: Mark's cardiomyopathy was identified through comprehensive medical assessments, including imaging tests and cardiac evaluations.

Overview: Mark Lee, a 45-year-old accountant, has been diagnosed with cardiomyopathy, a condition that results in the weakening of the heart muscle, leading to impaired heart function.

 Mark Lee - Symptoms: Shortness of breath, particularly during physical activities, Persistent fatigue and weakness, and Swelling in the ankles and abdomen.

 Mark Lee - Diagnosis: Mark's cardiomyopathy was identified through comprehensive medical assessments, including imaging tests and cardiac evaluations.

 Mark Lee - Treatment: Medications: Prescribed medications to enhance heart function and alleviate symptoms.  Lifestyle Changes: Adopted a heart-healthy diet, emphasizing low-sodium foods.  Engaged in regular, supervised exercise routines.

Alex Smith - Valvular Heart Disease 

Overview: Alex Smith, a 55-year-old architect, has been diagnosed with valvular heart disease, a condition affecting the proper functioning of the heart valves.

 Alex Smith - Symptoms:

Chest pain or discomfort.

 Irregular heartbeats.

metadata.window:
Sarah Davis - Congenital Heart Defects

Overview: Sarah Davis, a 30-year-old graphic designer, was born with congenital heart defects, structural abnormalities in the heart present from birth.

 Sarah Davis - Symptoms:

Shortness of breath, especially during physical activities.

 Cyanosis (bluish tint to the skin or lips) in severe cases.
